flavor_text_entries.red:
A rare and elusive
POKéMON that is
said to bring happiness to those
who manage to get
it.
flavor_text_entries.blue:
A rare and elusive
POKéMON that is
said to bring happiness to those
who manage to get
it.
flavor_text_entries.yellow:
A gentle and kind­
hearted POKéMON
that shares its nutritious eggs
if it sees an
injured POKéMON.
flavor_text_entries.gold:
It walks carefully
to prevent its
egg from breaking. However, it is
extremely fast at
running away.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
Few in number and
difficult to cap­
ture, it is said to bring happiness
to the trainer who
catches it.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
People try to
catch it for its
extremely nutritious eggs,
but it rarely can
be found.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
CHANSEY lays nutritionally excellent
eggs on an everyday basis.
The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even
those people who have lost their
appetite.

flavor_text_entries.sun:
The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients
and a favorite food of many Pokémon.
flavor_text_entries.moon:
Not only are these Pokémon fast runners,
they’re also few in number, so anyone who finds
one must be lucky indeed.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
It seems that other Pokémon’s efforts to take
its delicious, nutritious egg away from it caused
Chansey to get faster at fleeing.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
Because the eggs on their bellies have been
overharvested by people in the past, the
Chansey population remains very small.
flavor_text_entries.lets-go-pikachu:
A gentle and kindhearted Pokémon that shares
its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured Pokémon.
flavor_text_entries.lets-go-eevee:

flavor_text_entries.sword:
The egg Chansey carries is not only delicious
but also packed with nutrition. It’s used as a
high-class cooking ingredient.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
This species was once very slow. To protect their
eggs from other creatures, these Pokémon
became able to flee quickly.
flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus: This purehearted Pokémon shares its eggs with the injured.
